'''Hokkien'''
A dialect of Mandarin

'''Noun, Verb'''

One word from Singlish, N a modified version of English. Given meaning is afraid to die. Just used to describe people who are gutless. Usually only used by Singaporeans. Nevertheless its origin is from a Chinese dialect. Done in a humourous way of course. A fictious character from a Singapore drama called Mr Kiasu. Also the cousin of Mr Kiasu.

'''Kiasi'''

1. (conversation) (derogatory) a coward

          Why are you so Kiasi? You won't die just being getting a small cut on the finger.

2. (conversation) (derogatory) a nickname

          He is such a Kiasi, he does not have the guts to take a chances at anything.